# udev rules for HakoForge Hako-Core Powerboard
#
# Hand the data interface (1.1) from cdc_acm to hako_powerboard whenever
# cdc_acm binds to it. The board enumerates as a generic Arduino Leonardo
# (VID 2341, PID 8036), and cdc_acm's USB Communications class match
# auto-claims both the Comm interface (1.0) and cascades to the Data
# interface (1.1) before our driver gets a look. This rule rebinds 1.1
# to us at every boot and every device reconnect.
#
# WARNING: this rule is incompatible with HakoFoundry running concurrently.
# Once installed, /dev/ttyACM0 will not appear for the powerboard, so
# HakoFoundry will not be able to open the device. Install only after
# committing to a kernel-driver-only setup.
#
# WARNING: the match is on Arduino Leonardo VID:PID. If you have a real
# Arduino Leonardo on this host, hako_powerboard's probe will load, send
# V:, fail to parse, and return -ENODEV — the device will fall back to
# cdc_acm. /dev/ttyACM* on that Leonardo will appear with a brief delay.

ACTION=="bind", SUBSYSTEM=="usb", DRIVER=="cdc_acm", \
    ATTRS{idVendor}=="2341", ATTRS{idProduct}=="8036", \
    ATTR{bInterfaceNumber}=="01", \
    RUN+="/bin/sh -c '/sbin/modprobe hako_powerboard; echo $kernel > /sys/bus/usb/drivers/cdc_acm/unbind; sleep 0.2; echo $kernel > /sys/bus/usb/drivers/hako_powerboard/bind'"
